The theory is put into practice in the practical lessons by solving different exercises on computer. In Moodle environment there is a course description, schedule (topic/activity/exercises are written there according to the week), guide materials (study module), forum (for communication), mailbox (for sending individual e-mails), my results. Study materials are available on the Internet. The course is successfully finished, when all modules are assessed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives extra knowledge or evens up basic computer knowledge aquired from high school, which can be used in the future while studying and/or working. Using computer in study process should not be a problem by the end of this course. To ensure that, different topics are discussed during the course which have proven to be difficult in both studying and individual computer usage (e.g file formats and converting them, the Internet, protocols, browsers and searching information, security and privacy in the Internet, word and table processing). Compter programs and web environments which are available and necessary during studying in the faculty of medicine are used.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Description of the study process: Theory is put into practice by solving different tasks on computer. After short overview of the topic each student solves excercises individually and when necessary is instructed by the supervisor. Study materials in e-environment, forum or e-mail is used to solve problems. Solved excercises are sent to forum which is made for each module. To pass the evaluation successfully it is necessary to complete all excercises (individually or using help). After completing the evaluation all results are visible in the study environment.
Description of the modules: The course comprises different topics (modules). There are 8 modules. Each topic consists of short overview and excercises which are available with each module. There are also references to extra materials. Additional materials are also categorized by topics. It is possible to send memos and messages regarding topics that need attention through study environment using button "messages"
